"Abstract Anyone who has searched the Internet for products and services has experienced the wonderful assortment of products, services and resources that can be found online. We are witnessing the rapid growth of truly global commerce with unparalleled opportunity for choice and selection, competition and more. However, when criminals operating in another nation attack, the operators of E-commerce systems confront one of the most serious downsides of global operations since there is little or no commonality on how police officials in various nations will respond. Possible conflicts can arise in the absence of common codes of criminal conduct, standards of collaboration and consensus as to how the “civilized” forces of law and order will proceed against the denizens of the “dark side”."
